---
layout: "index.njk"
title: "Home"
---

{# ==== HEADER ==== #}
<header class="phd-live-header">
  <div class="header-left">
    <strong>*Process as Everything</strong> <p>an evolving research environment documenting my doctoral process in real time.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="header-right">
    <p class="header-note">Note: This site publishes my PhD research as it unfolds, including incomplete thoughts, experiments, and revisions.</p>
  </div>
</header>

<hr class="header-divider">

{# ==== TWO-COLUMN MAIN CONTENT ==== #}
<div class="phd-live-main">
  
  {# LEFT COLUMN: LIVE FEED #}
  <aside class="live-column">
    <h2 class="live-heading" id="live-heading">in progress</h2>
    <p class="live-subheading">latest activities</p>
    
    <div class="live-feed">
      {# Working sessions #}
      <div id="live-now"></div>
      <div id="live-next"></div>
      <div id="live-past-sessions"></div>
      
      {# Stream items #}
      <div id="live-stream"></div>
    </div>
  </aside>
  
  {# RIGHT COLUMN: STATIC INFO #}
  <section class="info-column">
    {# Research Focus #}
    <div class="info-section">
      <h2>Research Focus</h2>
      <p>This research explores how conversational AI tools are changing the way we learn, teach and think -- and what this means for our understanding of intelligence and knowledge. Rather than studying it from the outside, I am investigating this by building my own tools and systems, using my experience as both lecturer and student as the starting point.</p>      
      <p><em>Key questions include:</em></p>
      <ul>
        <li>How might AI transform teaching and learning — in my own work as a researcher and lecturer, and in higher education more broadly?</li>
        <li>What shifts can we expect in learning environments as technology evolves alongside social and political change?</li>
        <li>How can playful and speculative design methods help us imagine and build more creative and ethical forms of AI-augmented learning environments?</li>
      </ul>
      <p><a href="{{ '/phd-proposal/' | url }}" class="text-link">Read Proposal →</a></p>
    </div>
    
    {# Latest Posts #}
    <div class="info-section">
      <h2>Latest Posts</h2>
      {% set posts = collections.posts | default([]) %}
      {% if posts | length %}
        <ul class="post-list">
          {% for post in posts | reverse | limit(4) %}
            <li>
              <h3><a href="{{ post.url | url }}">{{ (post.data.title or post.fileSlug) | lower }}</a></h3>
              <small><time data-dt="{{ post.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.date | isoDate }}</time></small>
              {% set desc = post.data.description or (post.templateContent | striptags) %}
              <p>{{ desc | truncate(100) }}</p>
            </li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p class="more-link"><a href="{{ '/posts/' | url }}">Read all posts →</a></p>
      {% else %}
        <p>No posts yet.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    
    {# Featured Posts #}
    <div class="info-section">
      <h2>Featured Posts</h2>
      {% set featuredPosts = collections.featuredPosts | default([]) %}
      {% if featuredPosts | length %}
        <ul class="post-list">
          {% for post in featuredPosts | limit(3) %}
            <li>
              <h3>
                <a href="{{ post.url | url }}">{{ (post.data.title or post.fileSlug) | lower }}</a>
                <span class="badge">Featured</span>
              </h3>
              <small><time data-dt="{{ post.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.date | isoDate }}</time></small>
              {% set desc = post.data.description or (post.templateContent | striptags) %}
              <p>{{ desc | truncate(120) }}</p>
            </li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      {% else %}
        <p>No featured posts yet. Add <code>featured: true</code> to post front matter.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
    
    {# Upcoming Milestones #}
    <div class="info-section">
      <h2>Upcoming Milestones</h2>
      {% set ms = collections.milestones | default([]) %}
      {% if ms | length %}
        <ul class="milestone-list">
          {% for m in ms | limit(5) %}
            {% if not m.checked %}
            <li>
              <strong>{{ m.title }}</strong>
              {% if m.due %}
                <small>due <time data-dt="{{ m.due }}">{{ m.due }}</time></small>
              {% endif %}
              {% if m.url %}<a href="{{ m.url }}">view note</a>{% endif %}
            </li>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p class="more-link"><a href="{{ '/planning/' | url }}">See all milestones →</a></p>
      {% else %}
        <p>No milestones yet. Add <code>- [ ] … #milestone @YYYY-MM-DD</code> to any note.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </section>
  
</div>
